snippet.textDisplay:
I'm never buying an Xbox again. Enough is enough and 1 time was more than enough. 360 was okay, One(X) was okay too, but clearly rushed. Controller on batteries was a laughable solution.
PS3 and PS4 were incredibly satisfying and pleasant from starting the console to gaming itself. Aesthetics wise too.

It was interesting to listen to this presentation.
While I understand the need to increase loading data speed to games becoming much bigger with higher resolution textures and more details, I can't see the problem of loading games. Current games don't "suffer" much from those (with exceptions, of course). Someone who has no patience to wait up a couple of minutes should check a psychiatrist, because that isn't adequate behaviour.

By the way, the mentioned technology of loading up "active" game assets has been tested in Horizon.
snippet.textOriginal:
